[1] Case updates
- Wed 26 Jun 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://mailchi.mp/sante.gouv.cd/ebola_kivu_26juin19?e=77c16511ad

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 25 Jun 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 2277, of which 2183 are confirmed and 94 are probable. In total, there were 1531 deaths (1437 confirmed and 94 probable) and 628 people cured.
- 329 suspected cases under investigation;
- 12 new confirmed cases [all in North Kivu], including 4 in Mabalako, 2 in Beni, 1 in Oicha, 1 in Musienene, 1 in Masereka, 1 in Lubero, 1 in Kyondo, 1 in Butembo;
- 9 new deaths of confirmed cases, including 4 community deaths -- 2 in Beni, 1 in Oicha and 1 in Butembo; 5 ETC deaths -- 3 in Beni and 2 in Katwa [North Kivu];
- 2 new recoveries released from ETCs -- 1 in Butembo and 1 in Komanda [Ituri].

News
Figures of the response
-----------------------
- 142 871 people vaccinated;
- 69 279 346 people under control;
- 125 contaminated health workers;
-- 2 health workers from Mabalako and Butembo, including 1 vaccinated, are among the new confirmed cases;
-- the unvaccinated Butembo health worker died in the community after refusing to be followed up.
- the cumulative number of confirmed/probable cases among health workers is 125 (5% of all confirmed/probable cases), including 40 deaths.

