- Tue 25 Jun 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://mailchi.mp/sante.gouv.cd/ebola_kivu_25juin19?e=f96cddba3b

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 24 Jun 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 2265, of which 2171 are confirmed and 94 are probable. In total, there were 1522 deaths (1428 confirmed and 94 probable) and 626 people cured;
- 296 suspected cases under investigation;
- 18 new confirmed cases, including 7 in Beni [North Kivu], 3 in Mabalako [North Kivu], 2 in Butembo [North Kivu], 2 Mandima [Ituri], 1 in Vuhovi [North Kivu], 1 in Lubero[North Kivu], 1 in Manguredjipa [North Kivu], and 1 in Musienene [North Kivu];
- 12 new deaths of confirmed cases, including 7 community deaths --including 4 in Beni, 1 in Butembo, 1 in Mandima, and 1 in Mangurujipa; 5 ETC deaths -- 3 in Beni, 1 in Mabalako, and 1 in Katwa;
- 3 new recoveries released from Katwa ETC.

News
Partial resumption of response activities in Beni
-------------------------------------------------
- The activities of the response teams have partially resumed this Tue 25 Jun 2019 in Beni, after assessment of the situation between the coordination of the response of Beni and the security commission. Interviews were held with the families around whom the resistance had taken shape to appease the situation. In addition, a dialogue with young people from the health areas of Madrandelle and Tamende [North Kivu], where the security incidents took place, is scheduled for Wed 26 Jun 2019.
- On the WHO side, surveillance and vaccination activities have been temporarily suspended in Beni as well as in some remote areas of the city that require the use of vehicles. It should be noted that the 2 agents of response wounded in the incidents of 24 Jun 2019 are day laborers of the response supported by WHO

